FBIS4-61572 "drsov089_a_94017" FBIS-SOV-94-089 Daily Report 7 May 1994 INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Lithuania Refuses To Meet Kaliningrad Transit Demands Lithuania Refuses To Meet Kaliningrad Transit Demands MK0705085094 Moscow SEGODNYA in Russian 7 May 94 p 1 MK0705085094 Moscow SEGODNYA Russian BFN [Unattributed report: "Lithuania Refuses To Meet Kaliningrad Oblast's Demands"] [Text] A working meeting of expert groups of Lithuania and Kaliningrad Oblast on matters concerning transit to the Russian exclave on Lithuanian territory continued in Vilnius yesterday. Jonas Mackevicius, chief of the Foreign Ministry consular information department, was not optimistic about its possible chances of success. In his words, representatives of Kaliningrad set a number of requirements, particularly on granting them the right to drive by car without visas from Russia to Kaliningrad Oblast and back again, which Vilnius refused to meet.
